181
00:09:04.835 --> 00:09:08.375
Health targets are a means to achieve a policy objective,

182
00:09:08.715 --> 00:09:12.175
and they have well-known advantages and disadvantages.

183
00:09:13.445 --> 00:09:15.895
Some targets are clearly beneficial, such

184
00:09:15.895 --> 00:09:18.055
as the current target for child immunization,

185
00:09:18.915 --> 00:09:23.295
but many target indicators do not adequately stand for

186
00:09:23.295 --> 00:09:24.775
what we want them to stand for.

187
00:09:25.245 --> 00:09:27.735
Despite the best efforts of those, designing them

188
00:09:28.715 --> 00:09:32.015
two decades of research into health target implementation in

189
00:09:32.015 --> 00:09:34.335
New Zealand and elsewhere show

190
00:09:34.335 --> 00:09:37.495
that they often promote behavior that hits the target,

191
00:09:37.995 --> 00:09:39.135
but misses the point.

192
00:09:40.435 --> 00:09:41.475
Perverse incentives

193
00:09:41.975 --> 00:09:44.635
and unintended consequences such as gaming

194
00:09:44.695 --> 00:09:47.115
and cheating take root when clinicians

195
00:09:47.115 --> 00:09:48.875
and managers reach the limit

196
00:09:48.895 --> 00:09:51.115
of improvement within their control.

197
00:09:52.055 --> 00:09:55.035
And when this happens, particularly when resources are

198
00:09:55.035 --> 00:09:58.795
constrained, target achievement is prioritized over

199
00:09:58.795 --> 00:10:00.395
quality clinical practice.

200
00:10:02.505 --> 00:10:03.765
Any government is entitled

201
00:10:03.785 --> 00:10:06.165
to judge whether health targets are a suitable means

202
00:10:06.385 --> 00:10:08.125
for improving health service delivery.

203
00:10:08.865 --> 00:10:11.725
